Sentencas: The results of a study of the sulfur tolerance of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with composite anodes containing Cu, CeO2, and YSZ are presented.
Titulo: Highly sulfur tolerant Cu-ceria anodes for SOFCs

Sentencas: When operating a SOFC with Cu/CeO2/YSZ anodes on H-2 fuel containing sulfur impurities in the form of H2S at 1073 K it was found that H2S levels up to 450 ppm had no effect on anode performance.
Titulo: Highly sulfur tolerant Cu-ceria anodes for SOFCs

Sentencas: At higher H2S concentrations, anode deactivation was observed and can be attributed to the reaction of the CeO2 with H2S to form Ce2O2S. (c) 2005 The Electrochemical Society.
Titulo: Highly sulfur tolerant Cu-ceria anodes for SOFCs
